article.description: Davon Hayes scored 29 points and drilled seven 3-pointers and Southeastern Louisiana routed Florida A&M 108-69 on Monday night.
article.headline: Hayes scores 29 points, SE Louisiana routs Florida A&M
article.linkText: Hayes scores 29 points, SE Louisiana routs Florida A&M
article.story: HAMMOND, La. -- Davon Hayes scored 29 points and drilled seven 3-pointers and Southeastern Louisiana routed Florida A&M 108-69 on Monday night. Moses Greenwood hit 10 of his 12 shots for 23 points and Eddy Polanco added 13 for the Lions (6-4), who are 5-0 at home this season and topped the 100-point barrier for the first time since January 2015. Southeastern Louisiana hit 14 3-pointers and shot 58 percent overall. Desmond Williams scored 18 points and Marcus Barham added 14 for the Rattlers (2-8), who have lost seven straight after opening the season 2-1. Southeastern Louisiana led by 16 at the break and never let up in the second half. Hayes put the exclamation point on a 14-2 run with a dunk that gave the Lions a 60-34 lead. A Hayes 3 with 13:41 left pushed the lead past 30.
